sql:
SELECT (net_quantity_produced / run_time) * 100 AS production_efficiency
FROM production_data
WHERE production_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- Total net quantity is the net quantity of products produced; 
- Completed production status means the production process has finished; 
- Passed quality control status means the products have been checked and are of good quality.

sql:
SELECT production_shift, AVG(net_quantity_produced) AS avg_net_quantity
FROM production_data
GROUP BY production_shift;

SELECT production_id
FROM production_data
ORDER BY production_date ASC;

SELECT DISTINCT production_date
FROM production_data
ORDER BY production_date ASC;

external_knowledge:
- The quality control rate is calculated as (quantity_good / net_quantity_produced) * 100; 
- Production status 'completed' means the production process has finished; 
- Quality control status 'passed' means the production has passed the quality control check.

